    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Ads That Backfire</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jeremiah D Braunlin letter says ads placed on array of objects makes consumers loathe companies behind ads (Jan 15 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Anywhere the Eye Can See, It's Now Likely to See an Ad'' (front page, Jan. 15):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Anywhere the Eye Can See, It's Now Likely to See an Ad'' (front page, Jan. 15):</p>
        <p>Ads placed on eggs, airport baggage screening trays, elevators and hospital blankets merely create a public eye sore, making consumers loathe the companies behind such advertising even more than they already do.</p>
        <p>Jeremiah D. Braunlin  Cambridge, Mass., Jan. 15, 2007</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
